The senior management of the Department for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation (DPME) welcomed Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma on Friday. Dlamini-Zuma assumed her duties as the Minister in the Presidency today, meeting with Director General Mpumi Mpofu, Secretary of Planning Tshediso Matona, Statistician General Risenga Maluleka and Stats South Africa senior managers. Dlamini-Zuma has served as a Minister under Presidents Nelson Mandela, Thabo Mbeki, Kgalema Motlanthe and Jacob Zuma. She became the first woman to be appointed as the Chairperson of the African Union Commission. She said the DPME plays a critical role in ensuring that the National Development Plan vision for a prosperous country is put into practice through coordinated and focused Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation. -TNA Reporter 